       		<h2>Dosha</h2>
       		<p>There are three types of Dosha.  Vatta, Pitta and Kapha.</p>
          <p><strong>Vata</strong> -- Energy that controls bodily functions associated with motion, including blood circulation, breathing, blinking, and your heartbeat. </p>
          <p>In balance: There is creativity and vitality.</p>
          <p>Out of balance: Can produce fear and anxiety.</p>

          <p><strong>Pitta</strong> -- Energy that controls the body's metabolic systems, including digestion, absorption, nutrition, and your body's temperature. </p>
          <p>In balance: Leads to contentment and intelligence.</p>
          <p>Out of balance: Can cause ulcers and anger.</p>

          <p><strong>Kapha</strong> -- Energy that controls growth in the body. It supplies water to all body parts, moisturizes the skin, and maintains the immune system. </p>
          <p>In balance: Expressed as love and forgiveness.</p>
          <p>Out of balance: Can lead to insecurity and envy.</p>
